## Task 5: Pull and Run Images on Different Machines

### Learning Chunk 5A: Simulating Fresh Environment

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== TASK 5: Image Portability and Distribution ==="
echo "üéØ LEARNING GOAL: Demonstrate container portability"
echo ""
echo "REAL-WORLD SCENARIO:"
echo "‚Ä¢ Development team builds image"
echo "‚Ä¢ QA team pulls and tests on different environment"
echo "‚Ä¢ Production team deploys on production servers"
echo "‚Ä¢ All environments get identical application"
echo ""
echo "üßπ Simulating fresh environment by cleaning local images..."

# Stop any running containers
docker stop $(docker ps -q) 2>/dev/null || echo "No containers to stop"

echo "‚úÖ Stopped all running containers"
```

### Learning Chunk 5B: Clean Local Environment

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Cleaning Local Environment ==="
echo "Removing local copies to simulate pulling on a fresh machine"

# Remove local images (keep the pushed ones on Docker Hub)
docker rmi mywebapp:1.0.0 mywebapp:latest mywebapp:stable 2>/dev/null || echo "Some images already removed"
docker rmi mywebapp:dev mywebapp:staging mywebapp:prod 2>/dev/null || echo "Environment tags cleaned"
docker rmi ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp:1.0.0 ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp:latest 2>/dev/null || echo "Docker Hub tags cleaned locally"

echo ""
echo "üîç Verifying local images are removed:"
# Verify images are removed
docker images | grep mywebapp || echo "‚úÖ No local mywebapp images found - simulation successful!"
```

### Learning Chunk 5C: Pull from Docker Hub

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Pulling Images from Docker Hub ==="
echo "üåê Now we're acting like a fresh machine downloading our image"
echo "This could be a production server anywhere in the world"

# Pull latest version
echo "üì• Pulling latest version..."
docker pull ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp:latest

echo ""
# Pull specific version
echo "üì• Pulling specific version..."
docker pull ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp:1.0.0

echo ""
echo "‚úÖ Images successfully pulled from Docker Hub!"
```

### Learning Chunk 5D: Verify Pulled Images

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Verifying Pulled Images ==="
echo "üìä Let's confirm our images are now available locally"

# Verify the pulled images
docker images ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp

echo ""
echo "üîç IMAGE ANALYSIS:"
echo "‚Ä¢ Same image ID means identical content"
echo "‚Ä¢ Size should match what we pushed"
echo "‚Ä¢ Multiple tags can point to same image ID"
echo "‚Ä¢ Creation date shows when originally built"
```

### Learning Chunk 5E: Run Pulled Image in Production Mode

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Running Production Deployment ==="
echo "üöÄ Deploying as if this were a production server"

# Run in production mode with specific settings
docker run -d \
  -p 8080:80 \
  --name production-webapp \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  ${DOCKER_USERNAME}/mywebapp:latest

echo "‚úÖ Production container started with:"
echo "‚Ä¢ Port 8080 mapped to container port 80"
echo "‚Ä¢ Restart policy: unless-stopped"
echo "‚Ä¢ Named 'production-webapp' for management"

echo ""
echo "‚è≥ Waiting for application to fully start..."
sleep 3
```

### Learning Chunk 5F: Test Production Deployment

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Testing Production Deployment ==="

# Test with curl
echo "üåê Testing HTTP connectivity:"
curl -I http://localhost:8080

echo ""
echo "üìÑ Verifying HTML content delivery:"
curl -s http://localhost:8080 | grep "Docker Optimization Lab" && echo "‚úÖ Content verified!" || echo "‚ùå Content check failed"

echo ""
echo "üîí Testing security headers:"
curl -I http://localhost:8080 | grep -E "(X-Frame-Options|X-Content-Type-Options)" || echo "Security headers verified"
```

### Learning Chunk 5G: Monitor Production Container

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== Production Monitoring ==="

# Check container status
echo "üìä Container status:"
docker ps --filter name=production-webapp

echo ""
echo "üìã Container logs (last 10 lines):"
# View container logs
docker logs --tail 10 production-webapp

