## Complete Lab Cleanup

### Learning Chunk 7A: Organized Cleanup Process

```bash
echo ""
echo "=== COMPLETE LAB CLEANUP ==="
echo "üßπ Properly cleaning up all resources created in this lab"
echo "This demonstrates good Docker hygiene practices"

echo ""
echo "Step 1: Stop all running containers"
# Stop all containers
echo "üõë Stopping containers gracefully..."
docker stop $(docker ps -q) 2>/dev/null || echo "No containers to stop"

echo ""
echo "Step 2: Remove containers"
# Remove containers
echo "üóëÔ∏è  Removing containers..."
docker rm $(docker ps -aq) 2>/dev/null || echo "No containers to remove"
```

### Learning Chunk 7B: Image Cleanup

```bash
echo ""
echo "Step 3: Remove local images (optional)"
echo "‚ö†Ô∏è  This removes all local images - your Docker Hub images remain safe"

# List what we're about to remove
echo "üìã Images that will be removed:"
docker images --format "table {{.Repository}}\t{{.Tag}}\t{{.Size}}"

echo ""
read -p "ü§î Remove all local images? (y/N): " -r
if [[ $REPLY =~ ^[Yy]$ ]]; then
    # Remove images
    docker rmi $(docker images -q) 2>/dev/null || echo "Some images may be in use"
    echo "‚úÖ Local images removed"
else
    echo "üëç Keeping local images"
fi
```

### Learning Chunk 7C: System Cleanup

```bash
echo ""
echo "Step 4: Clean up Docker system resources"

# Clean up build cache and unused resources
echo "üßπ Cleaning Docker build cache and unused resources..."
docker system prune -f

echo ""
echo "üìä Final system state:"
docker system df

echo ""
echo "üßπ Optional: Clean up volumes (removes persistent data)"
echo "docker volume prune -f"

echo ""
echo "üìÅ Cleaning up project files:"
cd ..
rm -rf docker-optimization-lab
echo "‚úÖ Project directory removed"
```

